      <param name="arg.app.rawValue">cisco_cdr</param>
      <param name="arg.lookupName">call_quality_thresholds</param>
      <param name="arg.lookupName.rawValue">call_quality_thresholds</param>
      <param name="arg.exportFileName">call_quality_thresholds.csv</param>
      <param name="arg.fieldOrder">field min max quality</param>

      <module name="CustomBehavior">
        <param name="customBehavior">reloader</param>

        <module name="Tabs">
          <param name="name">selectedTab</param>
          <param name="staticTabs">
            <list>
              <param name="value">about</param>
              <param name="label">About</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">edit</param>
              <param name="label">Edit/Delete Thresholds</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">add</param>
              <param name="label">Add New Thresholds</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">download</param>
              <param name="label">Download CSV</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">reupload</param>
              <param name="label">Upload CSV</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">find</param>
              <param name="label">Find which quality stats are available</param>
            </list>
            <list>
              <param name="value">reset</param>
              <param name="label">Reset to defaults</param>
            </list>
          </param>

          <module name="Switcher" layoutPanel="panel_row1_col1">
            <param name="selectedGroup">$selectedTab$</param>


            <module name="NullModule" group="about">

              <module name="HTML">
                <param name="html"><![CDATA[
                <p>
                  CUCM has a powerful mechanism by which devices can report call quality metrics. The problem is that different classes and generations of devices will report different combinations of these metrics.  One class of devices might send jitter, latency and packet loss. Another set might send those plus the newer "Concealed Seconds" metrics.  Yet another group might send jitter, latency packet loss and MOS scores.  This means in the past whenever you needed to analyze call quality at a high level, you would be stuck fiddling with complex logic to deal with different fields, or often multiple reports to try and cover this complexity.
                </p>
                <p>
                  This app allows you to sidestep this problem by defining editable thresholds for any and all of those call quality fields.  With these thresholds in place we can automatically map each particular range of each metric to a specific call quality level, in the form of a single field called "quality".  Currently the four quality categories are hardcoded and are "good", "acceptable", "fair" and "poor" (and they are in that order).
                </p>
                <p>
                  With call quality thus normalized to this single reliable field you can run simple reports across all your CDR data, filtering by any extension or by any field on the CDR side if you like, and at the end build a chart with "quality" as one of the axes or as a split-by field.
                </p>

                <h3>Do you wish this was different or better?</h3>
                <p>
                  So do we!  but your opinions are more important than ours so please reach out to let us know them all by emailing <a href="mailto:support@sideviewapps.com">support@sideviewapps.com</a> !   We often surprise people by how quickly we can incorporate feedback and release new versions.
                </p>


                <h3>Advanced Note</h3>
                <p>
                  If you're a Splunk Admin, these settings are all contained in a single CSV lookup file at $$SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/cisco_cdr/lookups/call_quality_thresholds.csv on your SH/SHC. Thus you have the option of editing that file manually, or copying it around as needed.
                </p>
                ]]></param>
              </module>

              <module name="Button">
                <param name="label">Next</param>
                <module name="Redirector">
                  <param name="url">?</param>
                  <param name="arg.selectedTab">edit</param>
                </module>
              </module>

            </module>



            <module name="Filters" group="edit">
              <param name="name">filters</param>

              <module name="HTML">
                <param name="html"><![CDATA[

                ]]></param>
              </module>


              <module name="Search">
                <param name="search">| inputlookup $lookupName$ | head 100 | stats dc(*) as * dc(_*) as _* | transpose | rename column as field | table field</param>


                <module name="Pulldown">
                  <param name="name">field</param>
                  <param name="valueField">field</param>
                  <param name="float">left</param>

